sessions:
  - name: Preparing for Change, Rebellion, and Fun
    details: "You’ll start shaking up your mindset from Session 1 as you and your fellow Squadron members unpack how sales outreach is still stuck in the past (hint: it hasn’t changed in decades), how Rebels approach it differently, and what it really takes to break free from outdated tactics and fully step into your own Rebellion."
  - name: Handling common sales situations like a Rebel
    details: "By now, you’ll have built a campaign in the Campaign Creation Forum and it’s already on its way to catching your prospects’ attention. In this session, you’ll put Rebel prospecting into practice: using conversational, curiosity-driven language and adding emotional context that actually lands. The concepts are simple, but what do they really sound like in a live sales convo? Let’s find out."
  - name: Fellowship in the Follow-Up
    details: "You’ve heard the fortune’s in the follow-up and it’s true. But the real win is building genuine relationships. In this session, you’ll role-play follow-ups to your Rebel campaigns and learn how to spark real connection while naturally closing the next step by serving, not selling."
  - name: Rebels Overruling Objections
    details: "Chuck Norris handles objections by saying “Overruled” and moving on, but unless you're Chuck, you'll need a different approach. In this session, you’ll team up with your coach and Squadron to break down real objections, learn how to get prospects talking, drop curiosity-sparking landmines, and know exactly when to walk away."
  - name: Building Credibility
    details: "Trust and credibility are what turn curiosity into real buying intent. You’ve already created an experience with your Rebel campaign—now, this session shows you how to keep that momentum going and deepen the connection in your follow-up."
  - name: Refining Your Conversation
    details: "By now, you’ve had real conversations with prospects who’ve seen your Rebel campaigns. Maybe you’re crushing it—or maybe there’s room to grow. In this session, you’ll call your prospects live while your Squadron listens in, getting real-time feedback from your coach to sharpen your skills on the spot. Uncomfortable? Yep. Worth it? Absolutely."
  - name: Checkpoint - Your Trajectory
    details: "You’re halfway through your Squadron journey, and your second campaign is already in the wild. At this point, things look different: you’ve built pipeline, disqualified prospects, and hit some silence too. This session helps you reset your mindset, tackle new scenarios, and gear up to finish strong."
  - name: The Art of Storytelling in Sales
    details: "You’ve heard it before, “tell better stories.” Easier said than done. In this session, you’ll learn why storytelling works in sales, why most reps miss the mark, and how to start using it effectively with just a bit of fine-tuning and practice."
  - name: The Rules of Pleasant Persistence
    details: "Your Living Pipeline is now packed with characters: “Not Interested,” “Check Back Later,” Whales, Walruses, and more. While most reps lose deals by letting leads slip through the cracks, this session shows you how to follow up with persistence, personality, and purpose, just like a true Rebel."
  - name: Practice Makes Perfect
    details: "You’re 75% through your Squadron journey, and your third Rebel campaign is live. In this role-play-only session, bring real convo challenges or fine-tune your talk track, listening skills, and delivery with live practice and coaching to sharpen your edge."
  - name: Live Skills Challenge
    details: "As your Squadron journey nears its end, it’s time to lock in confidence. You’ll go live on calls again—putting feedback to the test, showing off your growth, and proving just how far you’ve come. (Oh, and maybe win some prizes, too.)"
  - name: Graduation and What’s Next
    details: "This final session brings it all home with a live Q&A, a moment of reflection, and a special guest appearance. Expect laughs, maybe a few tears, and a game plan to keep your momentum strong long after the Squadron ends."
